# Connect Frontend, Backend, and Database

The Postgres database is running via Docker and the backend application builds successfully. The reason the frontend and backend are not communicating is because the frontend (Android app) does not yet implement actual network requests for the authentication flow, and it may need network security configuration to allow local HTTP traffic to the backend.

## Proposed Changes

### Frontend Networking Configuration
We need to set up the Retrofit client to point to the backend and configure Android to allow cleartext traffic to the local emulator proxy (`10.0.2.2`).

#### [NEW] `frontend/app/src/main/java/com/example/supporterunt/app/network/NetworkModule.kt`
- Create a Retrofit instance configured with `http://10.0.2.2:8080/` as the Base URL (this maps to localhost:8080 on the host machine where the backend runs).
- Provide the [SupporterApi](file:///d:/Implementation4PJ/management_app_for_student/frontend/app/src/main/java/com/example/supporterunt/app/network/SupporterApi.kt#16-27) interface implementation.

#### [NEW] `frontend/app/src/main/res/xml/network_security_config.xml`
- Implement network security config to allow cleartext traffic for `10.0.2.2`.

#### [MODIFY] [frontend/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml](file:///d:/Implementation4PJ/management_app_for_student/frontend/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml)
- Add `<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />`.
- Add `android:networkSecurityConfig="@xml/network_security_config"` to the `<application>` tag.

